Spot Gold Declines for First Day in Three Before European Summit on Crisis

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-12-08T00:34:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-08/spot-gold-declines-for-first-day-in-three-before-european-summit-on-crisis.html
Gold for immediate delivery declined
for the first time in three days, falling as much as 0.3 percent
to $1,736.97 an ounce, and traded at $1,738.28 by 8:32 a.m.
Singapore time.  February-delivery futures slid 0.2 percent to
$1,742.20 an ounce on the Comex in  New York .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  